'''Sebastián Enzo Cáceres Ramos''' (born 18 August 1999) is a Uruguayan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Liga MX]] club [[Club América|América]] and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].

==Early life==
Cáceres was born on 18 August 1999 in the [[Nuevo París]] neighborhood of the capital city [[Montevideo]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://celestesporelmundo.com/sebastian-caceres-el-camino-de-la-resiliencia-y-la-superacion/|title=Sebastián Cáceres: El Camino De La Resiliencia Y La Superación|work=Celestes Por El Mundo|date=25 March 2025|accessdate=13 May 2025}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Cáceres is romantically involved and engaged with Mexican boxer and influencer Alana Flores.<ref>{{Cite news|url= https://www.tudn.com/futbol/liga-mx/alana-flores-tiene-fecha-boda-sebastian-caceres-america|title= Alana Flores adelanta la fecha de su boda con Sebastián Cáceres de América|website=TUDN|date=14 August 2025|accessdate=17 August 2025}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Liverpool Montevideo===
Cáceres made his professional debut on 26 August 2017 in a 2–1 loss against [[Peñarol]].<ref name="prodebut">{{cite web|title=Peñarol vs. Liverpool - 26 August 2017|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/08/26/uruguay/primera-division/club-atletico-penarol/liverpool-futbol-club/2559927/|accessdate=28 July 2020}}</ref> He scored his first goal on 24 February 2019 in a 4–4 draw against [[Centro Atlético Fénix|Fénix]].<ref name="fgoal">{{cite web|title=Fénix vs. Liverpool - 24 February 2019|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/02/24/uruguay/primera-division/centro-atletico-fenix/liverpool-futbol-club/2983887/|accessdate=28 July 2020}}</ref>
===América===
On 15 January 2020, Cáceres signed for [[Liga MX]] club [[Club América|América]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Club América finally announce Sebastián Cáceres signing|url=https://en.onefootball.com/%F0%9F%9A%A8-club-america-finally-announce-sebastian-caceres-signing/|website=OneFootball.com|publisher=One Football|language=English|accessdate=15 January 2020}}{{Dead link|date=December 2025 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}</ref>

==International career==
Cáceres is a former Uruguay youth international. He has represented Uruguay at the [[2019 South American U-20 Championship]], [[2019 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] and [[Football at the 2019 Pan American Games – Men's tournament|2019 Pan American Games]].<ref>{{cite web|title=3 - Sebastián Cáceres - AUF|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/3-sebastian-caceres/|access-date=28 July 2020}}</ref>

In September 2022, Cáceres was called up to the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]] for the first time.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lista de convocados para la próxima fecha FIFA|url=https://auf.org.uy/lista-de-convocados-para-la-proxima-fecha-fifa/|date=16 September 2022|access-date=24 September 2022|language=es}}</ref> He made his debut on 23 September 2022 in a 1–0 defeat against [[Iran national football team|Iran]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sebastián Cáceres debutó con Uruguay en la derrota ante Irán|url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/sebastian-caceres-debuto-con-uruguay-en-la-derrota-ante-iran|date=23 September 2022|access-date=24 September 2022|language=es}}</ref> On 31 May 2026, he was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

